entry.def: People sometimes say 'whoosh' when they are emphasizing the fact that something happens very suddenly or very fast.

example.ex: Then came the riders amid even louder cheers and whoosh! It was all over.
example.tran: 在更大的欢呼声中骑手们冲过来了，只听呼的一声，就全部飞奔而过！

entry.def: If something whooshes somewhere, it moves there quickly or suddenly.

example.ex: Cool air whooshes up through the grates on the street...
example.tran: 冷空气吹得大街上的格栅呜呜作响。

example.ex: Kites whooshed above the beach at intervals.
example.tran: 风筝在沙滩上空时隐时现。

entry.def: A whoosh of air or water is a sudden rush of it.

example.ex: ...the whoosh and murmur of the wind through the trees...
example.tran: 风吹过树林的呼啸呜咽
